      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NERANO NZ (9) is racing in peak form having made it back-to-back wins at this circuit when digging deep a fortnight ago. Draws wider but the form through the last win has been franked with the runner-up beating a good field last week and he steps up to a distance where he owns a good record. JILLIBY NITRO (10) had strong Victorian before placing in his last two outings here, coming from this barrier for third to Nerano two back before a 2m second last week. Proven at this longer distance and can make an impact again. GLITTER AINT GOLD (1) has been building towards a win with a string of good efforts from wider barriers. Suited up to a distance where he strikes at 50 per cent and should get his chance from the ace draw. Last-start winner SWEET ON LEXY (6) draws wider and goes up in grade but he could be capable of taking that step. SOUTH SEAS ROCK NZ (2) has trialled well since breaking last start. Kicked off in Sydney with a win from a wide barrier prior. Draws well so include.",
